<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-08-18T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-08-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="458" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/637: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-08-18T14:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 18,
                                        1927—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>318. Your 816, August 17, 10 p.m. Action outlined in your telegram of
                            August 17, 10 p.m., to Consulate at Shanghai is approved <pb facs="0512" n="404" xml:id="pg_404"/> by the Department. Department agrees with
                            you that Consul should not intervene in question of legal remedies.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>